FBIS4-41789 "drsov124_s_94003" FBIS-SOV-94-124 Daily Report 27 Jun 1994 Georgia Shevardnadze Makes Changes in Defense Ministry Shevardnadze Makes Changes in Defense Ministry LD2706192394 Tbilisi First Program Television Network in Georgian 1600 GMT 27 Jun 94 LD2706192394 Tbilisi First Program Television Network Georgian BFN [Text] In accordance with current structural changes in the Georgian Defense Ministry, by an edict of Eduard Shevardnadze, commander in chief of the Georgian Armed Forces, Major General Tamaz Dumbadze has been appointed a deputy defense minister responsible for emergency situations. Defense Minister Lieutenant General Vardiko Nadibaidze ordered that Colonel Vladimer Imnadze be appointed the first deputy chief of the General Staff of the armed forces.
